# Settings › Rekrutacja

Block `LBL_RECRUITMENT` (`m260601_…_recruitment_settings_menu.php`). Submenus:

| View | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `Transitions` | Whitelist `u_yf_recruitment_status_transitions` + `u_yf_recruitment_settings.configured` |
| `Workflows` | Relation workflow badges / create links (`RelationTrigger`) |
| `TransitionMail` | Mail matrix `u_yf_recruitment_status_transition_mail` (`short_name` + `delivery_mode` per `from_status`/`to_status`) |

Services: `RecruitmentStatusTransition`, `RecruitmentStatusTransitionMail`. Save: `Settings\Recruitment\Actions\SaveAjax` (`saveTransitions`, `saveTransitionMail`).

## Mail-on-transition (runtime)

- **Trigger:** kanban drag only, after successful `changeStatus()`.
- **Matrix:** stores **short names** (`u_yf_emailtemplates.sys_name`) + **`delivery_mode`** (`prompt` | `auto`) per row.
- **Resolution:** `RecruitmentStatusTransitionMail::resolveMailActions()` → per row `RecruitmentTemplate::resolveShortNamesForAccount()` for that short name; project `kontrahent` → account-specific template (`account_id` uitype 306 MultiReference), else global; account-specific hides globals.
- **`prompt`:** JSON `mailPrompt.templateIds` → `IndividualSendMailModal` + `Vtiger.js` `triggerSendEmailModal`.
- **`auto`:** server-side `RecruitmentStatusTransitionMail::sendAutoTemplates()` via `Outbound::sendFromTemplateParams`; JSON `autoSend` → toast in `Detail.js`.
- **Manual compose:** `IndividualSendMailModal` filters all `ProjektyRekrutacyjne` templates by same account tier when `sourceModule=ProjektyRekrutacyjne` + `sourceRecord`.
- **Gates:** `MassComposeEmail` on Candidates, `isActiveSendingMails`, default SMTP, candidate has email (`RelatedListLeftSideEmail::recordHasEmail` / `resolvePrimaryEmailField`).

## EmailTemplates (recruitment)

- **`sys_name`** required on Edit/Detail for `module = ProjektyRekrutacyjne`.
- **`is_system`** (checkbox on Edit/Detail): when set, template is hidden in manual compose (`SendMailModal`, `IndividualSendMailModal`); workflows/cron/matrix still resolve by `sys_name`. Recruitment compose templates (`Candidates`, `ProjektyRekrutacyjne`) default `is_system = 0`.
- **Accounts** optional via **`account_id`** MultiReference field (uitype 306 → Accounts, comma-separated IDs) on Edit/Detail; empty = global.
- Uniqueness: one template per `(sys_name, account)` for each linked account; one global per `sys_name`.
- Block delete/rename `sys_name` when listed in transition matrix.
- **`account_id`** field row visible only when Edit **Moduł** (`module_name`) = `ProjektyRekrutacyjne` (`Edit.js` toggle). After JS edits: minify `Edit.js`.
- Empty `sys_name` backfill: `m260618_000001` (+ `m260618_000002` iconv transliteration fix); slug via `iconv('UTF-8', 'ASCII//TRANSLIT//IGNORE', …)`.

## TransitionMail matrix UI

- URL: `index.php?module=Recruitment&parent=Settings&view=TransitionMail` — **not** `module=Settings` (handler not found).

- Per cell: checkbox → `.js-mail-templates-wrap` with **template pills** + add-template `<select>`.
- Each pill: short name + clickable mode badge (`prompt` ↔ `auto`, default `prompt`); `×` removes pill.
- CSS: `public/layouts/basic/modules/Settings/Recruitment/resources/TransitionMail.css` (registered in `TransitionMail.php` `getHeaderCss()`).
- Save payload: `entries[].templates[{ shortName, deliveryMode }]`.

Smoke: `docker compose exec -T app php tests/recruitment_status_transition_mail_smoke.php` — **clears** `u_yf_recruitment_status_transition_mail`; re-save matrix after run.

Dev pill fixture (no API): `https://dev.itconnect.pl/dev/transition-mail-pills.html` — `public/dev/transition-mail-pills.html`.
